ðŸ§  Pandas DataFrame Attributes
Pandas DataFrames have attributes that help you inspect the dataset.

| Attribute     | Description |
|---------------|-------------|
| df.shape      | Returns (rows, columns) |
| df.columns    | Returns column labels |
| df.index      | Returns row labels/index |
| df.dtypes     | Returns data types of columns |
| df.size       | Returns total number of elements |
| df.ndim       | Returns number of dimensions |

# Example
import pandas as pd

data = {
    'Name': ['Alice', 'Bob', 'Charlie'],
    'Age': [25, 30, 35],
    'Salary': [50000, 60000, 70000]
}
df = pd.DataFrame(data)

print("Shape:", df.shape)
print("Columns:", df.columns)
print("Index:", df.index)
print("Data Types:\n", df.dtypes)
print("Size:", df.size)
print("Dimensions:", df.ndim)

