ðŸ§¾ Handling Missing Values and Duplicates

- `isnull()` / `notnull()` â€“ Detect missing values  
- `fillna()` â€“ Fill missing values  
- `dropna()` â€“ Drop missing values  
- `duplicated()` â€“ Check duplicates  
- `drop_duplicates()` â€“ Remove duplicates

# Example
df_nan = pd.DataFrame({
    'A': [1, 2, None],
    'B': [None, 5, 6]
})
print("Missing values:\n", df_nan.isnull())
print("\nFill missing with 0:\n", df_nan.fillna(0))
print("\nDrop missing rows:\n", df_nan.dropna())

