ðŸ“Š Aggregation and Transformation Functions

- `sum()`, `mean()`, `max()`, `min()`, `count()`  
- `apply()` â€“ apply custom functions  
- `map()` â€“ element-wise transformation (Series)  
- `agg()` â€“ multiple aggregations

# Example
print("Mean Salary:", df['Salary'].mean())
print("Sum of Ages:", df['Age'].sum())

# Using apply
df['Age_squared'] = df['Age'].apply(lambda x: x**2)
print(df)

