ðŸ”— Merging, Joining, and Concatenation Functions

- `concat()` â€“ Combine DataFrames vertically or horizontally  
- `merge()` â€“ Merge DataFrames on keys  
- `join()` â€“ Join DataFrames by index

# Example
df1 = pd.DataFrame({'key':[1,2],'val':[10,20]})
df2 = pd.DataFrame({'key':[1,2],'val2':[100,200]})
df_merge = pd.merge(df1, df2, on='key')
print(df_merge)

